years earlier, the name had come into prominence as that of  Jane Shore , mistress of  King Edward IV  and subsequently of  Thomas Grey , 1st Marquess of Dorset, Lady Jane's grandfather. Jane Shore's tribulations in  1483  at the hands of  Richard III , Edward's brother and successor, became the subject of popular ballads and plays, which may well have increased the currency of the name in the 16th century. A 19th-century influence was its use as the name of the central character in  Charlotte Brontë's  novel Jane Eyre (  1847 ). From  1932 to 1959  it was used as the name of a cheerful and scantily clad beauty whose adventures were chronicled in a strip cartoon in the Daily Mirror. It is also borne by the American film stars  Jane Russell  (  1921–2011 ) and  Jane Fonda  (  b. 1937 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Johanna De Chisildene was born in 1311, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Richard De Chisildene. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Roger Le Waleys. She died in 1355, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1311–1355":"1311–1355","1310–1375":"1310–1375","1345–1383":"1345–1383","1350–1375":"1350–1375","1285–1332":"1285–1332","1345":"1345","1311":"1311","1355":"1355","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1375":"1375","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1383":"1383","after 1332":"pärast 1332","Langton Whaleys, Purbeck, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Purbeck, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Purbeck, Dorset, England":"Purbeck, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1311–1355":"1311–1355","1310–1375":"1310–1375","1345–1383":"1345–1383","1350–1375":"1350–1375","1285–1332":"1285–1332","1345":"1345","1311":"1311","1355":"1355","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1375":"1375","1285":"1285","1350":"1350","1383":"1383","after 1332":"1332 jälkeen","Langton Whaleys, Purbeck, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Purbeck, Dorset, 